==English==
===Etymology===
From [[w:John Dalton|John Dalton]], English chemist
===Noun phrase===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[Dalton]]'s [[law]]'''
#{{chemistry}},{{physics}} the [[total]] [[pressure]] of a [[mixture]] or [[gas]]es is the [[sum]] of the [[partial pressure]]s of each gas in the mixture; it is only true for [[ideal gas]]es
#{{chemistry}} when two [[element]]s can [[combine]] to form more than one [[compound]] then the [[amount]]s of one which combines with a fixed amount of the other will have a [[simple]] [[multiple]] [[relationship]]
===Synonyms===
* the law of partial pressures (1)
* the law of multiple proportions (2)
